<body>

<h1>FieldPass — Club Manager Guide</h1>
<p class="muted">For Club Managers: login, update club branding, and submit lineup before match day.</p>

<div class="box">
  <p class="req">Important rule (Lineup deadline):</p>
  <p>You should submit your player lineup <b>at least 24 hours before</b> the real match kickoff time. If you wait too late, the system/admin may lock the lineup and you may not be able to submit.</p>
</div>

<h2>1) Login (Club Manager)</h2>
<p class="muted">Club managers use the <b>admin portal</b> with <b>Malaysia (+60) mobile OTP</b> — the same flow as association admins (not username/password).</p>
<ol>
  <li>Open the admin login page in your browser (example: <b>http://localhost:8000/admin/login</b>).</li>
  <li>Enter your <b>mobile number</b> (national digits only, after +60 — no spaces).</li>
  <li>Click <b>Send OTP</b>. You will receive a one-time code (SMS/WhatsApp, depending on integration).</li>
  <li>Enter the <b>OTP code</b>, optionally tick <b>Remember me</b>, then click <b>Verify &amp; Sign In</b>.</li>
</ol>
<p class="muted">The phone number must match the one stored on your admin account. If login fails, ask your association admin to confirm your number under <b>Admins → Edit</b>.</p>

<h2>2) Update Club Logo</h2>
<ol>
  <li>From the left sidebar, go to <b>Clubs</b>.</li>
  <li>Find your club and click <b>Edit</b>.</li>
  <li>In the <b>Avatar / Logo</b> section:
    <ul>
      <li>Click <b>Choose File</b> and select a PNG/JPG image.</li>
      <li>Keep it square if possible (recommended for clean display in tables and headers).</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Click <b>Save / Update</b>.</li>
</ol>

<h2>3) Update Club Jersey (Home/Away)</h2>
<p class="muted">If your system shows jersey uploads (or “kit” images), update them the same way as the logo.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Go to <b>Clubs</b> → <b>Edit</b> your club.</li>
  <li>Locate the <b>Jersey / Kit</b> fields (Home / Away).</li>
  <li>Upload images (PNG/JPG) and click <b>Save / Update</b>.</li>
</ol>

<h2>4) Submit Player Lineup (24 hours before match)</h2>
<ol>
  <li>From the sidebar, go to <b>Matches</b> (or <b>Match</b>).</li>
  <li>Find the upcoming match for your club.</li>
  <li>Open the match and look for <b>Lineup</b> / <b>Player Lineup</b> / <b>Submit Lineup</b>.</li>
  <li>Select players for:
    <ul>
      <li><b>Starting XI</b></li>
      <li><b>Substitutes</b> (if the competition requires it)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Double-check:
    <ul>
      <li>Positions look correct (Goalkeeper / Defender / Midfielder / Forward).</li>
      <li>No missing required slots.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Click <b>Save / Submit Lineup</b>.</li>
</ol>

<h2>5) Common issues & fixes</h2>
<h3>A) I can’t see my club in the Clubs list</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Your admin account may not be assigned to the club yet. Ask the association admin/superadmin to assign your club under <b>Edit Admin → Assign Clubs</b>.</li>
</ul>

<h3>B) I can’t submit lineup / lineup is empty</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Check the competition has active clubs joined.</li>
  <li>Confirm your club has players assigned (Players → filter by your club).</li>
  <li>If it’s within 24 hours of kickoff, the match may be locked.</li>
</ul>

<h3>C) Logo doesn’t show after upload</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Refresh the page (Ctrl+F5).</li>
  <li>Make sure the file is JPG/PNG and under the size limit.</li>
</ul>

<h3>D) Players asking how to log in</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Players use the <b>player portal</b> (example: <b>/player/login</b>), not the admin URL.</li>
  <li>They sign in with the same <b>+60 mobile OTP</b> flow; their phone must match their player profile and status must be <b>ACTIVE</b>.</li>
</ul>

<p class="muted">Document version: 2026-04-02 (admin login: mobile OTP)</p>

</body>
</html>

